
    JUDGE President Dustan Mlambo today ordered President Jacob
Zuma to personally pay the costs of his failed attempt to stop the release of Thuli
Madonsela’s State of Capture report.Mlambo slammed Zuma’s legal attempt as an abuse of the
judicial system, labelling it “completely unreasonable” and “grossly remiss”.Mlambo also was very clear that the legal costs incurred
because of Zuma’s actions should not be for the taxpayer to cover, but must be
